                    <ul>
                        <li>Never give out personal information over the phone</li>
                        <li>Real banks won't ask for your password</li>
                        <li>If it sounds too good to be true, it probably is</li>
                        <li>Government agencies don't call about lawsuits</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="lesson-card">
                    <h2>üîí Phone Safety</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Let unknown calls go to voicemail</li>
                        <li>Don't press any numbers if you suspect a scam</li>
                        <li>Hang up and call the company directly</li>
                        <li>Always verify with a family member</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="lesson-card">
                    <h2>üíª Internet Safety</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Don't click on links in suspicious emails</li>
                        <li>Look for the lock icon in your browser</li>
                        <li>Use strong, different passwords</li>
                        <li>When in doubt, ask for help</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
